Package: hsical
Title: Hyperspectral Image Calibration Tool
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Maurycy", "Żarczyński", , email = "maurycy.zarczynski@ug.edu.pl", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A Shiny application for calculating pixel resolution from
    hyperspectral test scans. Determines pixel dimensions from motor positions
    and field-of-view settings, checks for square pixel geometry using a
    three-tier aspect ratio indicator, calculates the ideal FOV for square
    pixels, and provides comprehensive scan logging with structured YAML
    export for downstream processing in HSItools and Quarto.
